To the Same Person.

A good and wise man brings profit to the human race, even after his death. Of this, most illustrious Scipione, thy brother is a prooi, a man above my praise, and famed for his merits throughout the world. The books which he sent forth during his life, and ten times over corrected in every jot and tittle, these even Themis approves. Themis approves likewise those which, death forbidding, he could not publish. Now may affection drive thy soul on to bring to light his posthumous works. Hence, as gratitude is due to thy brother, the author, deep gratimde attends thee also.
